catalogue.definition:
This Data Item allows for a more convenient handling of the messages
at the receiver side by further defining the type of transaction.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    1. In applications where transactions of various types are exchanged,
       the Message Type Data Item facilitates the proper message handling
       at the receiver side.
    2. All Message Type values are reserved for common standard use.
    3. The list of items present for the four message types is defined in
       the following table.
       M stands for mandatory, O for optional, X for never present.

The list of items present for the four message types is defined in the following

catalogue.title: Message Type

catalogue.definition: Identification of the system from which the data are received.
catalogue.remark: NOTE - The SAC is fixed to zero to indicate a data flow local to the airport.
catalogue.title: Data Source Identifier

catalogue.definition: Type and characteristics of the data as transmitted by a system.
catalogue.title: Target Report Descriptor

catalogue.definition: Measured position of a target in local polar co-ordinates.
catalogue.title: Measured Position in Polar Co-ordinates

catalogue.definition: Position of a target in WGS-84 Co-ordinates.
catalogue.title: Position in WGS-84 Co-ordinates

catalogue.definition: Position of a target in Cartesian co-ordinates, in two’s complement form.
catalogue.title: Position in Cartesian Co-ordinates

catalogue.definition: Mode-3/A code converted into octal representation.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    1. Bit 15 has no meaning in the case of a smoothed Mode-3/A code
       and is set to 0 for a calculated track. For Mode S, it is set
       to one when an error correction has been attempted.
    2. For Mode S, bit 16 is normally set to zero, but can exceptionally
       be set to one to indicate a non-validated Mode-3/A code (e.g. alert
       condition detected, but new Mode-3/A code not successfully extracted).
catalogue.title: Mode-3/A Code in Octal Representation

values: Mode-3/A code derived from the reply of the transponder
Mode-3/A code not extracted during the last scan

catalogue.definition:
Flight Level (Mode C / Mode S Altitude) converted into binary two's
complement representation.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    1. The value shall be within the range described by ICAO Annex 10
    2. For Mode S, bit 15 (G) is set to one when an error correction has
       been attempted.
catalogue.title: Flight Level in Binary Representation

catalogue.definition:
Height above local 2D co-ordinate reference system (two's complement)
based on direct measurements not related to barometric pressure.
catalogue.title: Measured Height

catalogue.definition: Amplitude of Primary Plot.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    - The value is radar-dependent, 0 being the minimum detectable level
      for that radar.
catalogue.title: Amplitude of Primary Plot

catalogue.definition: Absolute time stamping expressed as UTC.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    - The time of day value is reset to zero each day at midnight.
catalogue.title: Time of Day

catalogue.definition:
An integer value representing a unique reference to a track record
within a particular track file.
catalogue.title: Track Number

catalogue.definition: Status of track.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    1. Some sensors are not be able to scan the whole coverage in one
       refresh period. Therefore, track extrapolation is performed in
       un-scanned sectors. CST is then set to 01.
    2. Bit-8 (GHO) is used to signal that the track is suspected to have
       been generated by a fake target.
catalogue.title: Track Status

values: Predictable extrapolation due to sensor refresh period (see NOTE)
Extrapolation due to unpredictable absence of detection
Tracking performed in 'Sensor Plane', i.e. neither slant range correction nor projection was applied
Slant range correction and a suitable projection technique are used to track in a 2D.reference plane, tangential to the earth model at the Sensor Site co-ordinates
Track merged by association to plot
Track merged by non-association to plot

catalogue.definition: Calculated track velocity expressed in polar co-ordinates.
catalogue.title: Calculated Track Velocity in Polar Co-ordinates

catalogue.definition:
Calculated track velocity expressed in Cartesian co-ordinates, in two’s
complement representation.
catalogue.title: Calculated Track Velocity in Cartesian Co-ordinates

catalogue.definition: Calculated Acceleration of the target, in two’s complement form.
catalogue.title: Calculated Acceleration

catalogue.definition: Target address (24-bits address) assigned uniquely to each Target.
catalogue.title: Target Address

catalogue.definition: Target (aircraft or vehicle) identification in 8 characters.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    - See ICAO document Annex 10, Volume I, Part I, section 3.8.2.9 for
      the coding rules.
catalogue.title: Target Identification

values: Callsign or registration downlinked from transponder

catalogue.definition: Target size defined as length and width of the detected target, and orientation.
catalogue.remark:
Notes:

    - The orientation gives the direction which the aircraft nose is
      pointing, relative to the Geographical North.
catalogue.title: Target Size and Orientation

Difference between the radial distance of the plot centre
and that of the presence.

items.description:

of the presence.
